    "description": "<p>You have a maximum number of <strong>Sorcery Points </strong>as shown in&nbsp;the Sorcery Points column of the Sorcerer Class Table. You can&nbsp;spend Sorcery Points instead of <strong>MP </strong>on Spell Enhancements.</p>\n<p>When you do, the total number of Sorcery Points and Mana&nbsp;Points can&rsquo;t exceed your <strong>Mana Spend Limit</strong>.&nbsp;</p>\n<p>Sorcery Point Conversion: You can spend <strong>2 AP</strong> to do one of&nbsp;the following:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 <strong>Sorcery Point</strong> to regain 1 <strong>MP</strong>.</li>\n<li>2 <strong>MP </strong>to regain 1 <strong>Sorcery Point</strong>.&nbsp;</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You regain any spent Sorcery Points when you complete&nbsp;a <strong>Long Rest</strong>.</p>",
